Discover Our Mission

Closing the GreenCycle Loop

From Vision to Mission

GreenCycle began as a grassroots idea hatched by high school students at GBS. In just two years, it has transformed into a powerful mission dedicated to revolutionizing Kuwait's approach to recycling and sustainability. We've collaborated with dedicated teachers, mentors, and peers to bring this ambitious project to life.

The Overconsumption Cycle

Kuwait faces a challenge in its consumption culture, generating massive waste that often ends up polluting landfills or being incinerated. GreenCycle addresses this by not only reducing the resulting waste but also by actively rewarding citizens for responsible disposal, making sustainability profitable for users.

Culture of Norm

Our ultimate goal is to create a culture where recycling is not just an option, but a deeply ingrained norm. We aim to establish a truly **GreenCycle** that fuels the sustainable future of Kuwait by making environmentally responsible behavior effortless and rewarding for everyone.

Model Evolution: Original vs. Vision

GreenCycle constantly innovates. See how our new Vision Model significantly upgrades efficiency and user experience compared to the Original GreenCycle prototype.

Feature Original GreenCycle (Prototype) GreenCycle Vision (Current)
Technology Infrared Sensor Dedicated AI / Computer Vision
Information Stored Local Storage (Machine Only) Specialized Cloud Drive Files
Points Communication Manually Sent Emails (1 to 6 hours delay) Instantly Sent Automatic Emails
Points Redemption Through Manual Contact/Arrangement Can be done through platform

The Road Ahead: Future Models

GreenCycle VisionPro

**The Material Sorter:** This machine will represent a significant leap, employing advanced AI to accept and meticulously sort a wide range of materials beyond standard plastic bottles (e.g., aluminum, specific plastics), maximizing resource recovery and expanding our environmental impact.

AI Sorting & Multi-Material

GreenCycle VisionLite

**Accessible Recycling:** Designed for scalability and accessibility, VisionLite allows people to use their own mobile devices to scan and deposit bottles. A sophisticated program ensures authenticated and accurate deposits, bringing the GreenCycle mission to every neighborhood.

Mobile Integration & Scalable
